###### BASH SHELL #######
Shell types:
1. Bourne shell (sh) 
2. C Shell (csh or tcsh)
3. Korn Shell (ksh)
4. Z Shell (zsh)
5. Bourne again shell (bash)

All shells have the Common purpose to facilitate between OS and USER.


To Check shell in use: ```markdown 
                          echo $shell
                          /bin/bash```


To change the shell from one to another:
```[~]& chsh
password:
Changing the shell for XYZ:
Enter the new Value or press for default.
    Login Shell[/bin/bash] :/bin/bash```


Bash Shell Features:
Alias-----> alias dt=date [To check date we can use the dt now]
History----> Lists Previously entered commands.

Bash Environment Variables
[~]$ echo $shell
     /bin/bash

[~]$ env-----> gives the all environment Variables.
[~]$ export---> To create a new environment

### BASH PROMT ####
[~]$
-~ =Present Working Directory.
$ =User Prompt Symbol

Customize the prompt variable using P1:
[~]$PS1="Ubuntu-Server:"
Ubuntu-Server

